<font color="#FF0000">MAYA LIN</font><br>
<tt>Mon Dec 23 23:08:43 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
Let's remeber something for just one moment.  Maya Lin was opposed to the flying of the American flag over the memorial.  She was also opposed to the beautiful and touching statues that have been added to the memorial.  In regards to the flag, it was the flag that we fought for and flew in every one of our bases in Vietnam.  It belongs there, regardless of what any one has to say about it.  Doesn't it seem that this woman has tried to exercise too much politics in her effort.  This monument doesn't belong to her, it belongs to America, all Americans.  I've been to the memorial and seen the names.  I looked up those names that were important to me.  I was there in Vietnam.  What disturbs me most about the memorial is how it's below ground.  This memorial is not to be hidden.  There was no shame in our service, Americans always respond to the call of their nation.  The men who made the ultimate sacrifice for a cause they didn't understand, shouldn't be hidden.  They should be honored and remembered for their sacrifice.  They gave all for a country that was mostly indifferent.  Yes, the monument is the focus of much emotion, but any monument that dealt directly woth Vietnam would.  Vietnam was a war of emotion for those of us that served and those of us that were home.  The wall is just a list of names, the faces of those men are lost except to those who remember them.  That is why the statues were created.  It was there to give a face to all those young faces that never got old.  That is why loved ones leave objects at the wall.  It is to make a completeness that Maya Lin's monument doesn't.  THIS ARGUMENT has nothing to do with race.  It has to do with a poor design and the selfish efforts of the designer to control the look of America's memorial.  No I am not a bitter, messed-up veteran.  I am a intelligent, open minded and suceesful citizen, that answered my county's call.  Maya Lin's politics don't belong anywhere near this memorial. 
<p><code>--   (Vietnam Vet) </code><p>


